	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, first, to address those who insist on talking about *killing* Lord Grimrot:<BR>
<BR>
He spawns at the undead ruins just to the Southwest of North Karana bridge. His placeholder is a skeleton that spawns directly underneath one of the little pavilions.<BR>
<BR>
**NOTE**  Someone mentioned that the PH should NOT be killed -- I don't know about this, I killed him and Grimrot showed up eventually, but maybe I just got lucky.<BR>
<BR>
The undead version of Grimrot looks just like a skeleton, so keep your eyes peeled.  He will always be carrying a scythe.  He is approximately level 30 and a few minor DOT's, but all in all, is fairly easy to kill. He drops a heart and a scythe. You DO NOT need the scythe the undead Grimrot drops, feel free to sell it.<BR>
<BR>
The live version of Grimrot is mid-30's. He has high magic resistance and harmtouch. He drops the scythe that you need.<BR>
<BR>
Hand these in to Cameland Serbold in the Temple of Life and he will give you the Aegis of Life.  Stats are:<BR>
Clerics, Paladins Only<BR>
MAGIC, LORE, NO DROP<BR>
9.5 Stone<BR>
12AC, 10WIS, 25 SV Disease<BR>
One charge of Superior Healing<BR>
<BR>
The real reason this item is so impressive is that it fits in the off-hand slot AND the back slot, making it one of the best back slot items in the game.<BR>
<BR>
Like people have said previously, the quest requires HIGH KINDLY faction. This can be attained by handing in bone chips or 2gp to Lashun Novashine, among other ways. Be careful all you Clerics of Bertoxxulous -- I've yet to find a way to raise faction with the Temple of Life that doesn't ruin my faction with the Bloodsabers =(<BR>
<BR>
OK.  Now on to the real meaning of this thread!<BR>
<BR>
For those of you who wish to parley with Lord Grimrot, a couple quests are first required.<BR>
<BR>
These are all given out by Kurne Rextulla in the Shrine of Bertoxxulous. The first involves killing Drosco, a named zombie, the second, killing Trumpy Irontoe.<BR>
<BR>
You give Trumpy's head to Kurne, who removes the skin from it and asks you to bring it to Grimrot so he might animate it and use the undead Trumpy as the field commander of his army.<BR>
<BR>
When you do this, Grimrot will speak with you about his former love, Arlena.<BR>
<BR>
Arlena is found in Mistmoore, in the ballroom. She spawns on the stage.<BR>
<BR>
Unfortunately, that is as far as I've gotten -- I have no specific information about Arlena at this point.<BR>
<BR>
I hope some of this has helped you guys!<BR>
<BR>
Erasmis Nightbringer<BR>
High Priest of Bertoxxulous, 39th order<BR>
Rodcet Nife
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
